In modern approaches, evolution is studied as a game of invasion requiring a winning trait to represent an evolutionary stable strategy (Smith and Price 1973). When looking at viral evolution from such a perspective, the concept of fitness seems questionable and sometimes even obsolete (Gyllenberg and Service 2011). In adaptive dynamics (Geritz et al. 1998), for instance, one evaluates the success of an invading viral strain (with trait \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
